subject: p14236258
History: History: M with hypotension at dialysis.
Findings: Left-sided dual lumen subclavian central venous catheter tip terminates within the proximal right atrium, coursing through a vascular stent within the left brachiocephalic vein and superior vena cava. Cardiac silhouette size is normal. Mild rightward deviation of the trachea with left superior mediastinal mass compatible with a known thyroid goiter is unchanged. Hilar contours are unchanged. Pulmonary vasculature is not engorged. Subsegmental atelectasis is noted in the lung bases without focal consolidation. No pleural effusion or pneumothorax is demonstrated. Marked degenerative changes of the left glenohumeral joints and remote right posterior rib are re- demonstrated.
